[5] Belize
Date: Thu 15 Jul 2010
Source: The Guardian [summ. & edited]
<http://www.guardian.bz/component/content/article/54-highlight/2057-dengue-hemorrhagic-fever-claims-5-year-old>


The Ministry of Health has been on high alert on the issue of dengue
and Dr. Jose Antonio Marenco, Director of Environmental Health
Program and vector control unit, says that there is an increase in
the numbers of cases in the Cayo and Belize Districts. There have
been 348 reported cases of classical dengue fever, 30 have been
confirmed at the Central Medical Laboratory and 42 have been
diagnosed as DHF. 142 cases have been recorded in the Cayo District
and 167 have been recorded in the Belize District. A 5-year-old girl
died of DHF on 13 Jul 2010.

