[6] Honduras
Date: Tue 20 Jul 2010
Source: People's Daily Online [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/90001/90782/90880/7073743.html>


This year [2010], 23 people have died of dengue fever in Honduras,
according to statistics released by the Honduran Health Ministry on
Monday [19 Jul 2010]. The number is nearly double last year's toll of
12. Health Minister Arturo Bendana said 22 000 [dengue virus]
infection cases were reported this year and 705 were the more
dangerous DHF (dengue hemorrhagic fever).

It was reported that regular meetings were held to study protection
measures and the financial ministry was asked by President Porfirio
Lobo to provide financial support for controlling the disease.

