[9] Indonesia (Yogyakarta)
Date: Tue 20 Jul 2010
Source: Tempointeractive [edited]
<http://www.tempointeractive.com/hg/nasional/2010/07/20/brk,20100720-264719,uk.html>


Around 45 community units in 14 sub districts in Yogyakarta have
become dengue fever endemic areas since 3 years ago. The number of
patients has increased as well. In 2009, there were 688 cases, with 5
dead people. Up until 19 Jul 2010, there have been 814 patients and
one dead person.

"Not one community unit in Yogyakarta is free from dengue fever
mosquitoes," said Rubangi, district surveillance officer of the
Yogyakarta Health Office, yesterday. However, this has not yet been
categorized as an extraordinary event.

[Byline: Muh Syaifullah]

